What you need to know:

Mr Boni Njenga’s mother sent him to the US in 2003 to keep him away from bad peer influence after his high school education. Today, Mr Njenga, an American citizen with a Master’s degree in Public Administration, is seeking to become the first Kenyan-American to sit as a commissioner in one of the county boards in the US.Mr Njenga is challenging first term incumbent Debbie Goettel, whom he acknowledges as a formidable opponent but adds that he is up to the task.  